.TH CXREF 1 "July 2026" "Kandelo" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
cxref \- generate a C-language program cross-reference table
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cxref
.RB [ \-cs ]
.RB [ \-o " file" ]
.RB [ \-w " num" ]
.RB [ \-D " name" [ =def ]]
.RB [ \-I " dir" ]
.RB [ \-U " name" ]
.I file ...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cxref
preprocesses and analyzes C source files, then writes a sorted list of C
symbols, their source paths, enclosing functions, and line references.
An asterisk before a line number marks a declaring reference.
Macro definitions and uses are included.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-c
Combine references from all input files into one sorted listing.
.TP
.B \-s
Do not print input filename headings.
.TP
.BI \-o " file"
Write the listing to
.I file
instead of standard output.
.TP
.BI \-w " num"
Limit output lines to
.I num
columns. Values below 51 select the default width of 80 columns.
.TP
.BI \-D " name" [ =def ]
Define a preprocessor macro.
.TP
.BI \-I " dir"
Add a header search directory.
.TP
.BI \-U " name"
Remove a preprocessor macro definition.
.PP
The order of
.BR \-D ,
.BR \-I ,
and
.B \-U
options is significant.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Zero indicates successful completion. A value greater than zero indicates an
option, input, preprocessing, parsing, or output error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR c17 (1)
